Week 9 In Class Work Thursday
By Nicholas Abbasi

Like:
Very clear information given about icons on map correlating to numbers in lists. Size of circles clearly based on numbers of confirmed cases of infection.
Color correlation consistent, when clicking on circle, it expands and shows confirmed in red, deaths in white and recovered in green.
Lots of useful links and information below map.
Last updated section clearly stated how date should be read.
Map updates throughout when clicking on list objects.

Dislike:
The about section could be titled better to clearly state its the about section.

Like:
Very interesting feature allowing an animated time lapse of the infection spreading.
Accurate location of infection circles.
The total infected is clear to see.

Dislike:
The range/legend for what circles indicate is somewhat lacking. Having the biggest circle being 50+ makes it so the information for one place having 55 infected versus 500 infected does not accurately show how sever the infection is. It does work in the sense of many close locations having it indicates the presence of a large infection, but not the best way to represent this. Size variations would work better.
Lacks clear information for real numbers of infected. Could use a list to show it better.

Like:
Very fleshed out time lapse feature that shows where in the bar graph and in the numbers the lapse is currently going through.
Shows the increase in numbers in each category, a unique feature I havent seen in the previous two.
Bar chart is very organized into selectable categories that give all desired information.
Able to see raw data in list form, with search bar.
Gives nice about section to show sources.

Dislike:
Although it looks good, the map generalizes areas of land into sections that dont accurately show where the infections are happening with in the sections.
